                <p rend="flushleft">I. <hi rend="italic">Report of the Deputies</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Council <hi rend="italic">adopted</hi> the order of items submitted by the
                    Deputies for the meeting (<gloss target="#t_CFM461">C.F.M. (46)</gloss>
                        25).<note n="96" xml:id="d90fn96">Not printed; the substance of the
                        Deputies’ Report, as presented orally by Couve de Murville, appears in the
                        United States Delegation Record of this meeting, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <pb facs="0223" n="203" xml:id="pg_203"/>
                <p rend="flushleft">II. <hi rend="italic">Allied Inspectorate in Italy and Treaty
                        Commission</hi>
                </p>
                <p>As no agreement was reached on this question, the Council passed on to the next
                    item.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">III. <hi rend="italic">Austro-Italian Frontier</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Council <hi rend="italic">adopted</hi> the proposal contained in the Deputies
                    Report to the following effect: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <list>
                            <item>“1) Having again considered the Austrian requests for the
                                rectification of the Austro-Italian frontier, the Deputies confirmed
                                that these requests do not represent minor rectifications within the
                                meaning of the decision taken by the Council of Foreign Ministers on
                                14th September 1945.</item>
                            <item>Consequently, the requests cannot be given consideration.</item>
                            <item>“2) The Austrian Government shall be officially informed of the
                                decision of 14th September 1945 and of the fact that their requests
                                are not considered consonant with that decision and can, therefore,
                                not be given consideration”.<note n="97" xml:id="d90fn97">The
                                    decision set forth here was communicated to the Austrian
                                    Representative Bischoff in a letter from the Council of Foreign
                                    Ministers dated May 3, 1946, the text of which was circulated to
                                    the Council as <gloss target="#t_CFM461">C.F.M. (46)</gloss> 39,
                                    May 3, 1946, not printed.</note>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">IV. <hi rend="italic">Next Meeting of the Council</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The proposal contained in the Deputies Report was <hi rend="italic">adopted</hi>:
                    the Deputies to meet in the afternoon at 4 p.m. in order to prepare the work for
                    the meeting of the Council of Foreign Ministers on Thursday, 2nd May, at 12
                    a.m.</p>
